UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2232
1 AN ACT relating to cosmetology.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 317A IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) A licensee shall not perform any of the following unless practicing under the
6 immediate supervision of a licensed physician:
7 (a) Botox or collagen injections;
8 (b) Laser treatments; or
9 (c) Any service that goes beyond the stratum germinativum layer, also known
10 as the basal layer of the epidermis.
11 (2) A licensee shall not perform any service regulated by another state board or
12 agency without the appropriate licensing for that service, including but not
13 limited to:
14 (a) Permanent makeup;
15 (b) Microblading; or
16 (c) Piercing.
17 Section 2. KRS 317A.010 is amended to read as follows:
