8 Section 3. KRS 317A.020 is amended to read as follows:
9 (1) A[No] person shall not engage in the practice of cosmetology, esthetic practices, or
10 nail technology for other than cosmetic purposes nor shall any person engage in the
11 practice of cosmetology, esthetic practices, or nail technology for the treatment of
12 physical or mental ailments. This chapter does not apply to:
13 (a) Persons authorized by the law of this state to practice medicine, podiatry,
14 optometry, dentistry, chiropractic, nursing, or embalming who perform
15 incidental practices of cosmetology, esthetic practices, and nail technology in
16 the normal course of the practice of their profession;
17 (b) Commissioned medical or surgical personnel of the United States Armed
18 Forces who perform incidental practices of cosmetology, esthetic practices, or
19 nail technology in the course of their duties; and
20 (c) Cosmetology, esthetic practices, or nail technology services performed at an
21 institution operated or under contract to the Department of Corrections or the
22 Department of Juvenile Justice[; and
23 (d) Persons engaged in natural hair braiding].
24 (2) Except as provided in subsection (1) of this section, a[no] person shall not engage
25 in the practice of cosmetology, esthetic practices, or nail technology for the public,
26 generally, or for consideration without the appropriate license required by this
27 chapter.
