3 Section 4. KRS 317A.030 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) There is created an independent agency of the state government to be known as the
5 Kentucky Board of Cosmetology, which shall have complete supervision over the
6 administration of the provisions of this chapter relating to the:
7 (a) Practice of cosmetology, esthetics, and nail technology;
8 (b) Instruction of cosmetology, esthetics, and nail technology;
9 (c) Salons where cosmetology, esthetics, and nail technology are practiced;
10 (d) Schools where cosmetology, esthetics, and nail technology are taught; and
11 (e) Practice, instruction, limited facility, or specialized course for any subset
12 skill of cosmetology, esthetics, or nail technology[cosmetology,
13 cosmetologists, schools of cosmetology, or esthetic practices or nail
14 technology, students, estheticians, nail technicians, instructors of
15 cosmetology, instructors of esthetic practices, or instructors of nail
16 technology, cosmetology salons, esthetic salons, and nail salons].
17 (2) The board shall be composed of seven (7) members appointed by the Governor as
18 follows:
19 (a) Four (4) of the members shall have been cosmetologists five (5) years prior to
20 their appointment and shall reside in Kentucky:
21 1. Two (2) of whom shall be cosmetology salon owners;
22 2. One (1) of whom shall be a cosmetology teacher in public education and
23 shall not own any interest in a cosmetology salon; and
24 3. One (1) of whom shall be an owner of or one who shall have a financial
25 interest in a licensed cosmetology school and shall be a member of a
26 nationally recognized association of cosmetologists;
27 (b) One (1) member shall be a licensed nail technician;
Page 10 of 25
BR223200.100 - 2232 - XXXX 3/27/2026 10:57 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2232
1 (c) One (1) member shall be a licensed esthetician;
2 (d) One (1) member shall be a citizen at large who is not associated with or
3 financially interested in the practices or businesses regulated; and
4 (e) None of whom nor the executive director shall be financially interested in, or
5 have any financial connection with, wholesale cosmetic supply or equipment
6 businesses.
7 At all times in the filling of vacancies of membership on the board, this balance of
8 representation shall be maintained.
9 (3) Appointments shall be for a term of two (2) years, ending on February 1.
10 (4) The Governor shall not remove any member of the board except for cause.
11 (5) The board shall elect from its members a chair, a vice chair, and a secretary.
12 (6) Four (4) members shall constitute a quorum for the transaction of any board
13 business.
14 (7) Each member of the board shall receive one hundred dollars ($100) per day for each
15 day of attendance at board meetings, and shall be reimbursed for necessary
16 traveling expenses and necessary expenses incurred in the performance of duties
17 pertaining to official business of the board.
18 (8) The board shall hold meetings at the place in the state and at the times deemed
19 necessary by the board to discharge its duties.
